1. What information do we collect?
We are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains the information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have about your information.

You control the information you provide. We collect personal information that you willingly share with us when you use our website. Here are some examples:

Information from forms: This includes contact forms, order forms, and newsletter signups. We might collect data like your name, email address, mailing address, and phone number.
Information from cookies and analytics tools: We may use cookies or similar technologies to collect non-personally identifiable information about your browsing activity. This could include pages visited, time spent on the site, and links clicked.
We take data security seriously. We use appropriate measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.

When you make a purchase, we use secure third-party payment processors like Stripe to handle your payment information. These processors adhere to strict industry standards and have their own privacy policies, which you can review on their websites.

We never share your personal information with any other third party for marketing purposes without your explicit consent.

 
2. What do we use your information for?
We use the information you provide and data collected through cookies and analytics for several purposes:

Personalize your experience: We use this information to tailor website content, recommendations, and functionality to your interests and preferences, ultimately enhancing your experience.
Enhance customer service: We use your information to answer your questions, address your concerns, and provide personalized support.
Fulfill your requests: We use your information to process transactions, deliver purchased products or services, and administer any contests, promotions, or surveys you participate in.
 

3. How we share your information?
We take the privacy of your information seriously. We do not sell, trade, or otherwise share your Personally Identifiable Information (PII) with outside parties without your consent. PII includes information that can be used to identify you, such as your name, email address, and billing information.

We may share your PII with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or servicing you. These parties are obligated to keep your information confidential.  Examples of such services might include payment processors or hosting providers.

We may also disclose your PII when required by law, to enforce our website policies, or to protect our or others’ rights, property, or safety.

Non-Personally Identifiable Information (Non-PII):

We may collect and share non-PII information with third parties for marketing, advertising, or other uses.  Non-PII information does not identify you personally. It might include things like browsing habits or website usage statistics.
By using our website, you consent to the collection and use of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.

4. Do we use cookies?
Yes, we use cookies. Cookies are small data files stored on your device by our website. They help us:

Remember you and your preferences:This saves you time by not having to re-enter information during future visits.
Improve your experience:Cookies allow us to understand how you use our website and make it better for future visitors.
Track website traffic:We use cookies to see how many people visit our site and how they interact with it. This helps us improve our overall service.
We may also use third-party cookies:
These cookies are set by other companies who provide services to us, such as analytics companies. These companies are not allowed to use the information collected on our behalf for their own purposes.

What information do cookies store?
Cookies may store a variety of information, including:

How long you spend on our website
The pages you visit
Your preferences (e.g., language)
Items added to your shopping cart (if applicable)
How to control cookies:
You can choose to disable cookies through your browser settings.

5. Security:
We take your data security seriously. We utilize industry-standard security measures to protect your Personally Identifiable Information, including:

Strong encryption algorithms
Regular software updates and patching
Strict access controls and user authentication
While no online environment is completely risk-free, we strive to provide a secure experience for our users. 
6. Data Retention:
We retain your Personally Identifiable Information (excluding payment and credit card information) for as long as necessary to:

Provide you with requested services
Comply with legal obligations
Resolve disputes
Protect our legitimate interests
7. Email Communications:
Service-related communications: We will send you essential emails regarding your project inquiries, web hosting, and website updates.
Promotional emails: With your permission, we may send you emails about new features or services. You can opt out of these emails at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link at the bottom of the email.

8. Privacy Policy Updates:
We reserve the right to modify this privacy policy at any time. If we make material changes, we may notify you through our website, email, or other means at our discretion. We will update the “Effective Date” at the top of this policy and any changes will supersede previous versions. We will not change our privacy policy in a way that reduces protections for user information collected in the past without the consent of the affected user.
